metadata.name: Celestial Collisions  #233
metadata.description:
Celestial Collisions  - The following series is an exploration of organic textures that embodies the way of a gentle breeze and the simulation of color pencils that randomly generates simple shapes. Out of 380K different combinations of the following combinations,
an endless amount of orientations can be produced from the piece of work.  

For the interactivity element, turn on the (a)toms and check the pulsar settings.. on the interval the atoms will go from being almost invisible to standing front and center. Sometimes, you may need to look hard depending on the various atoms. 

* 's' - save an image of the current state 
* 'a' - activate atoms

The piece is to be experienced by default at 1000x1000, however, have fun with the image. It will adapt to various sizes and create different images by whatever size you view it in. 

@generatecoll 2021

metadata.name: Complicare #18
metadata.description:
Complicare is my first "still" generative work, and an exercise in minimalism.

Inspired by pioneers like Sol Lewitt and Frank Stella, as well as current fx_hash artists such as Rev Dan Catt and Yazid, this work attempts to balance a diverse visual output with a restricted generative system. I also wanted to focus on honing my abilities to add texture to the digital canvas, taking cues from other great artists on here like William Mapan and Hevey.

Each piece has one of 17 different layouts and one of 6 different color palettes.

Thanks to all of the artists on fx_hash for inspiring me every day to make more art, and particularly to dcarcher for some really insightful artistic perspective and feedback.

metadata.name: Outside your Window #18
metadata.description:
Never take for granted that we sit in the safety of our homes, behind our windows, sheltered from the elements outside. 

The characteristics of the rain outside the window, and the window itself, will be determined by the mint hash. However, the background color of this piece will constantly change based on the hour of day it is loaded, hence note that the thumbnail will only technically be accurate 1/24 hours out of the day as it represents a static snapshot taken at the time of token rendering.

100% of the primary proceeds will be donated towards flood relief efforts for the devastating December 2021 floods in Malaysia.

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: The Climb #142
metadata.description:
The climb is about the search for purpose.

Everyone needs a purpose, a path that leads somewhere. Whether you reach it or not is not the point, it’s about the climb. The search for a purpose gives our life meaning. It gives us a reason to look for something more.

Unfortunately, there is no universal truth as to what your purpose in life is. Everyone is unique. Different. We are the product of our upbringing, environment and the cumulative sum of thousands of microdecisions. We need to find meaning for ourselves. Our unique meaning. On this path, we climb alone.

“The Climb” is created to be raw, unique, beautiful and violently volatile, much like our lives.


Everything is written in javascript and p5js.
It can sometimes take a little while to render on older computers.

metadata.name: the Horizon #19
metadata.description:
I am interested in and pay attention to repeating patterns in nature. Searching for the possibility of depicting this rhythm, texture, and space opens this opportunity as a new experience for me. And how can I convert time to image? In this work, I have depicted the circle of wandering, like the sun that fluctuates in every horizon and climate, sometimes hot and tense and sometimes its rays like the morning breeze caressing our face, calling us to a new beginning. Where is your sun on the horizon, and what time is it in your world?
Made in p5js
Created July 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: Precision: micro #387
metadata.description: Precision: micro is the next entry in my "Precisions" series. It focuses on smaller shapes in smaller spaces, where individual elements are placed, overwritten, removed, and sectioned out.  My previous Precisions pieces used exact placements to reach a sense of balance, but with micro, I've introduced removal as an instrument of balance.

metadata.name: After rain #4
metadata.description:
It's been raining.
After the rain, the night city becomes clean and bright.
After the rain, the night city plays with hundreds of lights.
After the rain, life becomes brighter.

This work was created thanks to the help of my wife, she is an artist, her description of the stages of creating paintings was embodied in the algorithm of this work. Working with brushes, paints and shapes, working with layer sequences, etc.

The palette ranges from black and white to rich colors, try it, look for what you like best.
Easter egg available...

metadata.name: Sneronoi #104
metadata.description:
Stochastic neighbor embedding meets Voronoi tessellation.

Images are generated by gradient descent and the optimization process is shown as an animation. Each piece is considered final when the animation stops. There are 11 different color palettes and two distinct input point arrangements, allowing for a wide range of distinct visual outputs. Made with D3.

Press 's' to save as svg.

Press 'p' to save as png (4000x4000).

Author:
Claus O. Wilke
https://clauswilke.com/art
https://twitter.com/clauswilke

metadata.name: Deep Space Grid - AI Study III #29
metadata.description:
Deep Space Grid uses experimentation with lines, shapes, color and opacity through the exploration of faux space charts.

Adjusts to monitor size, best viewed in fullscreen mode.

This project is a generative art experiment using a Text2Code workflow. The JavaScript code for this project was written entirely by AI using GPT-3. None of the code was altered or created by a human aside from changing Math.random() with fxrand().

Text2Code study #3 /// Project CoDexter by @BrainArtLabs

metadata.name: In the woods : close-up #15
metadata.description:
Part of the « In the woods » collection, this project was born after an inspirational walk in the woods.

This project includes different features depending on the size of the elements, the number and colors used, the different shapes, the ambient light… 

Please note that the preview image is a little bit more saturated than the real token.

In Open Live window, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image (you can change DP in the URL to  a greater value for an even larger resolution).

Visit https://sites.google.com/view/tidally-disrupted-star/ for the genesis description of the "In the woods" collection.

The first drop of this collection is still available : https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/5574

All remaining editions will be burned after a short period of time.

Twitter: @TidallyD
